    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hunter</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 121.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 24, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 7th instant, No. 68,
                            together with its enclosure upon the subject of certain reports, to the
                            effect that a negotiation was in progress in Canada for the purpose of
                            making peace between the United States and the insurgents, has been
                            received. The information concerning the condition of the insurgent
                            government, and the situation of their affairs, which it is presumed
                            will have reached you ere this, cannot but make you aware of the falsity
                            of the allegation.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. HUNTER, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,&amp;c.,&amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
